              <tr> 
                <td height="622" valign="top" colspan="2" bgcolor="#004142">&nbsp;<table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4"><tr bgcolor="#000000"><td><font color="#FFFFFF"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial" size="6">The Problems With BH Ships</font></td></tr></table><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td></td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Rating</Font></TD><TD><IMG SRC="images/a4.gif" BORDER=0><A HREF="articleread.php3?article=1636"><IMG SRC="images/aread.GIF" BORDER=0></A><A HREF="articlereview.php3?article=1636"><IMG SRC="images/areview.GIF" BORDER=0></A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Author</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="../membercenter/directory/memberpage.php3?member=3327">Jodo "Jodo Kast17" Kast</A></FONT></TD></TR><!-- 3327 --><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Description</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">The problems with using bounty hunter ships as a space fleet by themselves.</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Article</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">   Before I get blasted by all of your BH ship fans our there, let me say this.  I am not against the use of bounty hunter ships.  In fact, they are in all of my decks, but alone, they are not enough to win in space.<br>
   Bounty hunter ships have been a great benefit to scum and villainy decks.  It is the first time that a Scum deck can actually have some space power.  They have great abilities, which work wonderfully in combination with Imperial ships.<br>
   I am seeing an increasing number of decks, especially court or land based decks that use nothing more than the bounty hunter ships as their space protection.  Yes, when brought together en mass they are very good, but against an EBO or Hidden Base deck they become very weak.	Only one ship out of the group is good enough to hold a system alone that is Boba Fett in Slave 1.  Zuckuss is good, but cannot hold out against any battle destinies.	In straight up fighting, with no added pilots, Boba Fett will beat the Super Falcon because he can draw battle destiny.  I have seen decks with only bossk as their ship.  This is crazy, bossk can add a destiny, yes, which makes him great with another ship, but he had no immunity to attrition.  Dengar is great with someone else, cancels immunity to attrition, but he cannot draw battle destiny.<br>
   Even gathered together the ships are not the best option.  Allow me to demonstrate their combined abilities:<br>
   Power: 27 (pretty good)  Deploy: 31!   Forfeit: 23 (not worth the cost of deploying)  Destinies: 3 (if you start, 2 if defending)  Added Benefits: Opponent must have ability six to have destiny and has no immunity to attrition.<br>
   Now, I can deploy 4 plain old regular star destroyers for 32 force, get power 32 and have forfeit 36.<br>
   The power of bounty hunter ships is in their game text.  Not their power.  If you are depending on the fear of the ships to drive opponents away, it is no longer around.  People realize they are not indestructible.  When combined with the good old star destroyers or some of the new interceptors they are deadly combinations, but alone they are not good enough.<br>
   The biggest weakness of the bounty hunter ship is its deploy and forfeit.  Only dengar has the same deploy as forfeit, and he only has 5/5.	Bossk is 8/5, not a good ratio.  Towards the end of the game a single star destroyer is good enough to hold a system with a drain of 3 because it has enough forfeit to cover most battle damage.  The bounty hunter ships can easily turn into problems when a high battle destiny is drawn and two of them have to be lost at the same time.<br>
   Bounty hunter ships are great assets to any deck.  They have great game texts that will often damage an opponent (dengar takes out home one without trouble) but they should remain in their place.	They are additions to a fleet, not the fleet itself.  They cannot be depended on to have space dominance or even compete in space alone.  They work best with high power and forfeit ships that can take damage and allow them to add their abilities.<br>
 </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><a href="articles.php3"><img src="images/aback.GIF" border="0"></a><A HREF="articleread.php3?article=1636"><IMG SRC="images/aread.GIF" BORDER=0></A><A HREF="articlereview.php3?article=1636"><IMG SRC="images/areview.GIF" BORDER=0></A><a href="articleprint.php3?article=1636" TARGET="BLANK_"><img src="images/aprint.gif" border="0"></a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> </td>
